  <description><![CDATA[<p>The luxurious Grand Hotel Covento di Amalfi clings high to the cliffs 80 metres above <a data-udi="umb://document/f13578bcd0ea422bb13fbbbc34693d47" href="/{localLink:umb://document/f13578bcd0ea422bb13fbbbc34693d47}" title="Amalfi Coast">Amalfi’s</a> harbour and boasts panoramic sea views and a rich history.</p>
<p>Dating back to the 13th century, this former monastery has been carefully refurbished using local materials and meticulous attention to detail. The interiors have a minimalist and contemporary style, with crisp white hallways broken up with old black and white photos showing the hotel’s history. Guest rooms are all individually sized but include modern amenities and sea views come as standard.</p>
<p>Convento di Amalfi boasts one of the best locations on the Amalfi Coast and the design of the hotel ensures the stunning coastal views can be enjoyed from nearly everywhere. A small infinity pool hugs the edge of the cliff side, while two restaurants have plenty of tables on the large terrace meaning you can relax with a leisurely meal while admiring the sea and colourful buildings of Amalfi.</p>]]></description>
